Author: JOLLIE
Vol / Page: 17
Edition:
Quote: Watt, who was starting a sheep-farm in the Wairau Valley [before 1850 was] on `Thirds' for three years. This meant one third of the wool and lambs each year to Watt and I have two thirds.
