Date: 0/0/1939
Source: First White Boy Born in Otago
Author: BEATTIE
Vol / Page: 100
Edition:
Quote: Johnny Jones saw that Trotter was a reliable man and gave him a start [in the 1850s] with a flock of 1000 sheep on thirds - that is to say, Jones got the wool and two-thirds of the lambs while Trotter got one-third for his work.
Notes:

